retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}, {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050107495683596405", "url": "https://x.com/0x_KaELo/status/2050107495683596405", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/0x_KaELo/status/2050107495683596405", "text": "The early neobanks changed how we access money. \nRevolut, Monzo, Chime, and N26 replaced physical branches with sleek mobile apps and raised billions to do it.\n\n Yet beneath the surface, the same old systems remained: \n>> Third-party custodians.\n>> Slow SWIFT transfers.\n>> Multi-day settlement times, and those familiar \u201caccounts under review\u201d messages.\n\n@useTria takes a different path. \n> Launched as a programmable. neo-finance built from the ground up in 2026.\n> It delivers a single self-custodial account that feels seamless from day one. \n> Hundreds of thousands of users already move, trade, and spend inside this unified environment every day.\n> Inside that one account you hold two powerful trading venues that share the same wallet and the same deep liquidity.\n\n On mobile, Decibel delivers fast, intuitive perpetuals execution designed for speed on the go. \n\nOn the desktop, Hyperliquid offers low-fee, high-efficiency trading built for precision and scale. \n\nYou never fragment your capital or break your flow. \nWhether you start on your phone or your screen, everything stays connected.\n\nThe experience extends beyond trading. Profits do not sit idle.\n A built-in global card lets you spend directly from the same balance, turning every gain into immediate purchasing power wherever you are in the world.\n\nTria\u2019s incentive system reinforces this loop. \n> For every ten dollars traded you earn one XP. \n> Your first perpetual trade awards 250 XP. \n> Higher trading volume unlocks upgraded card tiers and the Tria Badge.\n> Each upgrade delivers lower fees and stronger multipliers.\n> So the more you engage, the more efficient the entire system becomes.\n\n Trade, earn, upgrade, reduce costs, repeat. The cycle compounds naturally.\n\nMobile or desktop no longer matters. Every action feeds the same account, the same rewards, the same liquidity pool. \n\nThe only question left is where you begin: \nMobile with Decibel or desktop with Hyperliquid? \n\nThe account is already waiting.\nPowered by @MindoAI", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 35, "likeCount": 34, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 150, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 06:58:10 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 0, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050107495683596405", "displayTextRange": [0, 291], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "0x_KaELo", "url": "https://x.com/0x_KaELo", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/0x_KaELo", "id": "260806007", "name": "C A L", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2033781415826083840/favnkk9J_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/260806007/1753490504", "description": "", "location": "", "followers": 13349, "following": 7304, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": false, "createdAt": "Fri Mar 04 16:54:52 +0000 2011", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 231189, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 4441, "statusesCount": 246200, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2010296044874252524"], "profile_bio": {"description": "writer \ud83d\udcdd || web3 \ud83c\udf10 || crypto \ud83e\ude99 || Arsenal fan \ud83d\ude09 || . DM for ADs\ud83d\udc8c", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "t.me/Ox_KaELo", "expanded_url": "http://t.me/Ox_KaELo", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/5xlhIXeyyy"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {"media": [{"display_url": "pic.twitter.com/vD1HPGLlKK", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/0x_KaELo/status/2050107495683596405/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"all": {"tags": [{"name": "Tria", "screen_name": "useTria", "type": "user", "user_id": "1022556475850256384"}]}, "large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050107488494624768", "indices": [292, 315], "media_key": "3_2050107488494624768", "media_results": {"id": "QXBpTWVkaWFSZXN1bHRzOgwAAQoAARxzceYbFyAACgACHHNx58eWIHUAAA==", "result": {"__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHNx5hsXIAAKAAIcc3Hnx5YgdQAA", "media_key": "3_2050107488494624768"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHNx5hsXIAAs0s4.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 573, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 88}, {"h": 661, "w": 661, "x": 257, "y": 0}, {"h": 661, "w": 580, "x": 297, "y": 0}, {"h": 661, "w": 331, "x": 422, "y": 0}, {"h": 661, "w": 1024, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 661, "width": 1024}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 661, "w": 1024}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/vD1HPGLlKK"}]}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": [{"id_str": "1022556475850256384", "indices": [356, 364], "name": "Tria", "screen_name": "useTria"}, {"id_str": "1937544417835130880", "indices": [2002, 2010], "name": "Mindo AI", "screen_name": "MindoAI"}]}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}, {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050105698504081853", "url": "https://x.com/Falalu83/status/2050105698504081853", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Falalu83/status/2050105698504081853", "text": "TGIF!\n\nThe first wave of fintech got rid of the bank branch.\n\nRevolut, Monzo, Chime, N26 - clean apps, huge funding, better UX. But underneath? Same rails. Same custodians. Same delays, same \u201caccount under review\u201d emails when it mattered most.\n\nThe second wave is going deeper.\n\nWith projects like @useTria, the bank itself gets unbundled. Your balance sits in a wallet you control. Yield is built-in. Payments move globally in seconds, not days, without correspondent banks in the middle. The card spends, but there\u2019s no hidden custodian holding your money behind the scenes.\n\nIt\u2019s not just a crypto app - it\u2019s what finance looks like when you design it fresh instead of layering on top of 50-year-old infrastructure.\n\n--------------------------------------\n\nAt the same time, another layer of the stack is getting rebuilt: security.\n\n@quipnetwork just rolled out a new direction focused on future-proofing Bitcoin itself. Not by changing Bitcoin, but by adding a quantum-resistant layer on top. Using post-quantum cryptography, it aims to protect wallets from a scenario where current encryption could eventually break.\n\nNo forced migrations. No protocol wars. Just an opt-in layer that upgrades how keys are secured, especially for older BTC sitting in vulnerable address types.\n\nDifferent angles, same idea:\n\nOne rebuilds how money moves. The other rebuilds how it\u2019s protected.\n\nBoth assume the old system doesn\u2019t get fixed - it gets replaced piece by piece.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 16, "replyCount": 29, "likeCount": 33, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 160, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 06:51:02 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 0, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050105698504081853", "displayTextRange": [0, 277], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "Falalu83", "url": "https://x.com/Falalu83", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Falalu83", "id": "356400954", "name": "Falalu", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1946485843440308224/Yu1gOpuR_normal.jpg", "coverPictur